40|$|On January 1, 2007, the Electric Reliability Council of Texas (ERCOT) market {{became the}} first {{restructured}} market in the US to completely remove <b>caps</b> on the <b>prices</b> which could be charged to residential energy consumers by the retailers associated with the traditional or incumbent utility service providers. Our analysis suggests that the expiration of the price-to-beat (PTB) <b>price</b> <b>caps</b> {{may have led to}} a reduction in the average prices charged by competitive retail electric providers (REPs). Electricity market restructuring Electricity <b>prices</b> <b>Price</b> <b>caps...</b>|$|R
