2500|$|As of 2013, {{construction}} costs were estimated at $12.8 billion, 22% over the 2008 budget, plus $4.7 billion {{in research and}} development costs. [...] Because of budget difficulties, the Chief of Naval Operations, Admiral Jonathan Greenert, warned there might be a two-year delay beyond 2016 in completing Gerald R. Ford. The GAO reported that the <b>price</b> <b>cap</b> would be met by the Navy accepting an incomplete ship for that cost.|$|E
